            "type": "text",
            "text": "In modern API infrastructure, efficiently handling background tasks is crucial for scalability and user experience. Ben2 for background processing offers a robust solution for offloading asynchronous operations, allowing API teams to maintain responsive services while managing complex workflows."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Features of Ben2 for Background Tasks"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ben2 for background processing is designed to handle long-running or resource-intensive tasks outside the main API request cycle. It supports features like task queuing, automatic retries, and real-time status updates. For API teams, this means reduced latency in client-facing endpoints and improved fault tolerance. Integration typically involves configuring Ben2 endpoints to accept task payloads and setting up webhooks for completion notifications."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
