        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and Scalability Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When deploying Ben2 for background workloads, monitor key metrics like task throughput and error rates. Scale Ben2 instances horizontally based on queue depth, and implement caching for frequently accessed data to reduce load. For high-traffic APIs, consider partitioning tasks by type or user segment to optimize resource allocation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices for Production Environments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Adopt idempotent task designs to prevent duplicate processing during retries. Log all Ben2 interactions with correlation IDs for traceability, and set up alerts for abnormal task durations. Regularly review and update timeout settings based on historical performance data to balance efficiency and reliability."
          }
        ]
